  <title class="- topic/title ">Create an Offer Folder</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">As the number of offers you create
	 increases, it is often useful to use offer folders to keep your offer list
	 organized. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
    <context id="context_E1F34DE12EC0420E8C12F0A4F46437EC" class="- topic/section task/context ">
      <p class="- topic/p ">When working with folders, consider a naming
		  convention or approach. Clients often use the current month, the type of
		  offers, the location of the offer on the site, or even the campaign as the
		  naming convention. 
		</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_F7A8DC0A7ACA4205AB52F42AF21CD0AF" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
      <step id="step_419128739B764645BD636D81453CAC66" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Offers</uicontrol><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> List</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_DB347A39CDC9480EBF1FF75EDEE5A4FB" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click the down arrow at the top of
			 the offers folders list, then click 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Add</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_00706DAC192A4E16BBDC26C6FF81EC09" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Name the folder. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <?xm-replace_text Step Result?>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
